Not quite sure, I just had a night straight out of the soap operas..even to see it is to disbelieve it.<br>
<br>
Met a girl online..stupid thing, yes I know. Getting along just dandy. She sent me picutures, very pleasing to the eyes. I sent her pictures, apparently satisfactory. Two weeks go by, she lived 15 minutes from my house but refused to meet me. So I told her I was done. Never met a girl online before and the refusal to put it off line was too wierd. So she caves, and I meet her. WTF is this? I meet her, but it is a girl I already knew from the mall by my house. The girl that came over realised that the jig was up and confessed that some random girl payed her to come over to my house and pretend it was her. She did not count on us knowing eachother. <br>
<br>
So, me and the girl that I already knew decided to own this random psychotic. We set up a meeting in the mall for today, and I have my brother come by and recognize this girl (as the girl who she really is, not the girl she is pretending to be (confused yet?))<br>
<br>
It turns out the actual girl I have been talking on the phone with these past few weeks was this gargantuan girl who was pretending to be the sister of the other girl the entire time. The thing she did not count on in her game (whatever that was) is that I knew the girl she payed to pretend she was the first girl. <br>
<br>
So in the end, the gargantuan girl got proved to be a lying sack of scheisse in the middle of the mall. Would this end it? No..she called the police and alleged assault charges on me. First of all, anyone who knows me knows that I would rather pay a crack head to shoot me than harm a female no matter the circumstances. The plus side is that the girl who was paid and was really my friend let me know the cops were on the way to the mall. I stuck around and found the police officer. I offered my story and the girl who was paid to be the other girl stayed on as my witness, the gargantuan girl was proved to be a complete liar and was told by the police officer that it was a good idea to never contact me again.<br>
<br>
Thouroughly confused? So am I. I was expecting Candid Camera to jump out at any second.<br>
